de.esoco.lib.property

Interface HasProperties

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ColumnDefinition, DataSet<T>, MutableProperties
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractDataSet, AbstractStringProperties, DoubleDataSet, IntDataSet, SimpleColumnDefinition, StringDataSet, StringProperties

    public interface HasProperties
    An interface that defines the read access to named properties. The property access methods have a default value parameter that is returned if an instance doesn't contain a property value for a particular property name.

    It is up to subclasses to implement the storing of properties. This means that it depends on the implementation, which datatypes are supported to be stored. Trying to store or access unsupported types may cause an exception.
